# Client build-time config. Vite inlines VITE_* at BUILD time, so these must be
# set wherever the build runs:
#   • Local:  copy this file to apps/client/.env and fill in the values.
#   • Prod:   set the same names as Railway service variables — the Dockerfile
#             declares matching ARGs so they bake into the static bundle.
#
# Both values here are safe to expose in client-side code:
#   • a Web3Forms access key is a public submission key
#   • VITE_PORTAL_ORIGIN is just the provider's public URL
#
# The Discord webhook is NOT here on purpose: it is a write-capable secret and
# must never ship in the bundle. Discord delivery is proxied through the portal
# provider's /api/inquiry endpoint, which holds the webhook server-side (set
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL on the provider service, NOT as a VITE_ var).
#
# HireMe sends every submission to ALL configured channels. With neither set,
# the form falls back to opening a prefilled mail draft (handy for local dev).

# Web3Forms access key — emails each Hire-Me submission to you.
# Free, tied to your email: https://web3forms.com  (Create Access Key)
VITE_WEB3FORMS_KEY=

# Portal provider origin (e.g. https://portal.layerdynamics.co). When set, each
# Hire-Me submission is POSTed to ${VITE_PORTAL_ORIGIN}/api/inquiry, which
# forwards to Discord server-side. Leave empty to skip the Discord channel.
VITE_PORTAL_ORIGIN=
